    },
    {
      "block_id": "1978-01_02-heading-1235c04045-1",
      "kind": "heading",
      "text": "SCORE ORIENTEERING",
      "text_length": 18
    },
    {
      "block_id": "1978-01_02-paragraph-f25db3f33d-1",
      "kind": "paragraph",
      "text": "In a SCORE ORIENTEERING EVENT, the area chosen for competition is covered with a large number of Control Points. The Control Points are weighted, according to the difficulty anticipated in finding them. Points are selected for both the novice and the experienced Orienteer. This event requires the competitors to locate as many Control Markers as possible within the one-hour period. Points are awarded for each Control Point found, and deducted for being on the course for more than an hour. Competitors are given a map of the area and sent out at two (2) minute intervals. The map shows each control point and its point value. Choose the route you feel is best for you. A good event is one that has all the Control Points found, but having no one person finding them all within the allotted time.",
      "text_length": 798
    },
    {
